		"body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nThe current settings dialog in Joplin does not provide a way to quickly locate specific options. Users have to manually browse through multiple sections, which becomes inefficient as the number of settings grows.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nThis PR adds a search functionality to the settings dialog (`ConfigScreen.tsx`).\r\nIt allows users to filter and locate settings based on their input.\r\n\r\nKey features:\r\n\r\n* Real-time filtering of settings\r\n* Matches based on setting titles and descriptions\r\n* Improves accessibility and navigation within settings\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n1. Open the Joplin desktop app\r\n2. Navigate to the Settings dialog\r\n3. Enter text in the search bar\r\n4. Verify that:\r\n\r\n   * Relevant settings are filtered correctly\r\n   * Non-matching settings are hidden\r\n   * Clearing the search restores all settings\r\n",
