			"updated_at": "2026-03-19T18:46:52Z",
			"body": "## Test Plan\r\n\r\n### Screen Recordings\r\n\r\n**Normal Testing of the Search Bar in Settings:**\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ce911f7e-dba9-490c-a823-3a922640b561\r\n\r\n**Testing of Search Bar in Settings with Screen Reader (Windows Narrator) On:**\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/01e7f7b8-db54-4288-8a65-5e5f3bef5448\r\n\r\n### Manual Testing\r\n- Opened Settings and verified search bar appears at the top\r\n- Typed in search box and confirmed settings filter in real time\r\n- Cleared search and confirmed all settings return\r\n- Switching sidebar sections resets the search term correctly\r\n- Tested on light and dark themes — styling adapts correctly\r\n\r\n### Accessibility\r\n- Tested with Windows Narrator — announces \"Search settings\" correctly when focused\r\n- TabIndex={-1} ensures the input does not interfere with arrow key \r\n  navigation between tab panels\r\n\r\n### AI Policy\r\nI confirm this PR was written by me. AI tools were used only for \r\ndebugging assistance, not to generate the core implementation.",
